title: For Sale:  Xenonics SuperVision Nightvision Monocular
postcontent:
For sale is a SuperVision Night Vision Monocular by Xenonics.  I am the original owner of this unit and purchased it in early 2015 but have not had the need to use it as much as I had hoped.  Total usage has been less than 20 hours.  Below is some useful information on the device as well as links to relevant information. The Supervision night vision device is different from other standard systems in that it uses digital technology to amplify ambient/infrared light, displaying a black and white image as opposed to a green one. Even compared to the most advanced traditional Generation 3 devices, Supervision offers superior clarity, resolution and range. Additional features include a reinforced housing, 2-8x zoom magnification, high resolution display, rechargeable lithium-ion battery, hand strap and carrying case.  Weight: 20 oz. Technical InformationNotes:•This monocular uses digital technology, a sensor powered by a signal processor, to pick up ambient infrared light•The display is a black and white high resolution image•The manufacturer states that this technology exceeds military-grade generation 3 night vision devices•An automatic gain control with three presets allows adjustments from twilight to dark night•Housed in a water-resistant polymer casing•Weighs 20 oz•Rechargeable lithium-ion battery and AC charger are included•The battery is removed from the monocular to charge it, please note that the battery may not be charged when the monocular is shipped, so it will require charging•When the monocular is powered up, the display will show "INIT" for a few moments as the circuits run a diagnostic check, this is not a defect•Includes carry bag and hand strapSpecifications:•Resolution 1280 x 768 pixels•Minimum illumination 0.0003 lux•Magnification 2x to 8x zoom•Focus 2 ft to infinity•Diopter adjustment +2 to -6•Field of view 525 ft at 1000 yds•1 year manufacturer's warranty
 
SuperVision Compared to Gen 3 PVS 14 - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NGnKWLHMN_U
 
Xenonic Inc. have already will start shipping what they call the most powerful night-vision scope in the world (that's what they say). SuperVision is a digital viewing system that uses a highly sophisticated and sensitive CCD sensor (380k pixels), which can digitally process information into a sharp clear picture on a high resolution display.SuperVision scope's performance exceeds even the best Military Grade GenIII Night Vision Goggles. Some pluses for the Xenonics Scope: higher clarity, better resolution and further range. It's also offering a 2 x to 8 x zoom magnification, something that was not achieved by the pack of night vision goggles manufacturers. Military-grade night vision actually requires you to install a 3 x magnifier which only gives one level of magnification at the expense of greater bulk and weight. At only 20 ozs., SuperVision is powered by a lithium-ion rechargeable battery (110 V charger included) .The big problem is that the SuperVision looks like a tiny astronomical telescope that can be used only if you hold it with one hand. So, there's no way you can mount it on your helmet or your gun. Don't worry though! It comes with a hand strap so there's no need to try finding your pocket when silver bullets are aimed at you. Just let it hang and use the effective no hands strategy, eh? But if you really want to face Predator, better stick with the Military Grade Generation 4 night vision goggles.If you want it, look for more info from SuperVision authorized dealers as soon as Xenonics Holdings Inc. touts that their piece is out. It will sell for a cent short of 1,400 $.Read more: http://news.softpedia.com/news/SuperVision-Offers-High-Powered-Digital-Night-Vision-51860.shtml#ixzz4BSpSzI4f

title: For Sale:  The Kimber Ultra Carry II, USED BUT IMMACULATE! LIKE NEW! L@@K!
postcontent:
OVERALL DESCRIPTION! NOT MINE!:INCLUDES ALL THE HOLSTERS PICTURED 3 SETS OF GRIPS, kIMBER NIGHT SIGHTS 3 MAGS 2 BOXES AMMO AND SELF DEFENSE AMMO ... ALL INCLUDED!!!CALL OR TEXT JIM @ REDACTED $600 FIRM!The Ultra Carry II from Kimber is accomplished with Kimber’s usualattention to detail. Weight of the pistol is 25 ounces, accordingto Kimber’s own stats, putting it at over three quarters of a poundless weight than a full size 1911. The weight factor is important,because in many ways we’re talking about a more compact version ofa Commander size pistol. The Commander, when it was originallyintroduced by Colt, had an aluminum alloy frame.
There was much chest beating about aluminum alloy frames holdingup, but aluminum alloy frames have proven to be quite acceptablefor hard duty with a heavy caliber pistol.
Barrel length is where this pistol is quite radical. The barrel isonly three inches long, making it 1-3/4 inches shorter than aCommander and a half-inch shorter than the Detonics CombatMaster.Magazine capacity with the pistol is a full seven rounds, as intraditional 1911 pistols.
Overall length of this pistol is 6.8 inches. The slide is stainlesssteel and the trigger is match grade aluminum. The added length inthe grip in order to accommodate seven rounds allows getting theentire last three fingers on the grip frame.
Danny and I both shot the Kimber Ultra Carry II using Federal 230grain Hydra Shok ammunition. I did my best shooting of the sessionwith the Kimber and this did not surprise me. In my hands, it shotslightly to the left, which is a chronic problem with myshooting.
My group was nice and tight. It should be remembered that I wouldsometimes test fire more than thirty 1911-style automatics in asession, so that even with my lackluster marksmanship, I tend to dobetter with a .45. Danny is also a good hand with a .45 and got abetter group than mine, both of us well within the parameters setfor the test. The pistol was quite pleasant to shoot and perceptionof recoil was not a factor.
Kimber recommends that, with the Ultra Carry models, the recoilspring should be changed every 1800 rounds. I had asked one of mycontacts at Kimber about swapping recoil springs as often asrecommended in their manuals. It was made clear to me, as I hadassumed, that once you hit the magic number of rounds you shouldn’texpect catastrophic spring failure. Instead, Kimber views this as away to ensure there will not be spring failure. That certainlymakes sense.
Sights on the Ultra Carry II are fixed and extremely rugged. Theyare left black and, if this pistol were mine, I would add whitemarkings on the sights to assist my older eyes. The thumb safety issingle sided, but extended, and the grip safety features a beavertail. The beaver tail amply protects the web of the hand. TheKimber Ultra Carry II is a classy looking pistol and performedquite well.

title: For Sale:  NFA TRUST
postcontent: An NFA Trust is STILL the best option for to to have an NFA item!NFA Trusts are extremely effective in managing NFA items, especially with BATFE's requirement that only "responsible persons" can have access and possess the NFA item(s).  Using the NFA Trust will give you flexibility in your management of the trust property, allowing you the option to appoint other law abiding individuals as "responsible persons," to help avoid any unlawful possession or use of those NFA items.I provide you with a tried-and-true Trust.  I am an Ohio Attorney and I have structured this Trust to give you flexibility in your ability to possess and use NFA items.  Additionally I will talk to you personally to make sure the Trust fits your desires in legally using and possessing NFA items.Please note that applications processed after July 13, 2016 will require the "Responsible Persons" to submit finger prints and a background check.  Additionally you must notify your local CLEO of your purchase (there is no longer the requirement for your CLEO to approve of any transaction, instead, you are required only to notify them of the pending transaction).  Trust is structured to limit the "responsible persons" to the Trustees, which decreases the paperwork needed to submit your applications for processing.  Also understand that using an NFA Trust will give you the flexibility to appoint and remove Trustees at your discretion.I provide a basic NFA Trust for $300.00Call to discuss how to tailor a NFA Trust to your needs!Attorney Eric S.
